            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>
                This page demonstrates basic CSS styling and how the Box Model works.
                By adjusting margins, padding, and borders, you can control the spacing
                and layout of elements in a web page.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section id="section2" class="content-section">
            <h2>The CSS Box Model</h2>
            <p>
                Every HTML element is treated as a rectangular box, which consists of:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Content</strong> – the text or image inside the box</li>
                <li><strong>Padding</strong> – space between the content and border</li>
                <li><strong>Border</strong> – the edge surrounding the padding</li>
                <li><strong>Margin</strong> – space between this element and others</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="section3" class="card-container">
